data.content:
## What Changed

.NET 10's `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` upgraded to **Microsoft.OpenApi v2**, which targets **OpenAPI 3.1** (JSON Schema-based). Here are the breaking changes in your code:

### 1. `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace removed
All `OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, etc. are gone. Examples are now `System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonNode`.

### 2. `OpenApiSchema.Nullable` removed
OpenAPI 3.1 uses JSON Schema's type model. Nullability is a flag on the `Type` property (`JsonSchemaType.Null`).

### 3. `OpenApiReference` restructured
The generic `OpenApiReference { Type = ..., Id = ... }` pattern is replaced by typed reference classes in `Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References` (e.g., `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference`).

---

## Fixed Code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;          // replaces Microsoft.OpenApi.Any
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References; // typed reference classes

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        // OpenApiString → JsonValue
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    // Typed reference replaces OpenApiSecurityScheme + OpenApiReference
    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                // Nullable property removed; clear the Null flag instead
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

### Summary of replacements

| .NET 9 (OpenApi v1) | .NET 10 (OpenApi v2) |
|---|---|
| `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` | `using System.Text.Json.Nodes` |
| `new OpenApiString("1.0")` | `JsonValue.Create("1.0")` |
| `schema.Nullable = false` | `schema.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` |
| `new OpenApiSecurityScheme { Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" } }` | `new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2")` |
